# Toolbox — Cursor Rules

## Non-negotiable constraints

1. FILES NEVER LEAVE THE BROWSER. No file uploads to any server. All processing is client-side WASM.
2. ENGINES ARE PURE TYPESCRIPT. packages/engines/ has zero React or UI imports.
3. USE DESIGN TOKENS. All styles use CSS custom properties (var(--color-*), var(--space-*), etc). No hardcoded hex values. No Tailwind.
4. NO CROSS-FEATURE IMPORTS. features/image/ never imports from features/pdf/. Shared code goes in packages/shared/.
5. ZUSTAND FOR JOB STATE. Never use useState to track job arrays. Use useToolJobs(TOOL_ID) hook.
6. STRICT TYPESCRIPT. exactOptionalPropertyTypes is on. Never assign T|undefined to optional T. Always null-check indexed access.
7. EVERY TOOL HAS A MANIFEST. Register in apps/web/src/registry/registry.ts.

## Package imports
- Design system:  @toolbox/design-system
- Shared types:   @toolbox/shared/types
- Shared consts:  @toolbox/shared/constants
- Job store hook: apps/web/src/hooks/useToolJobs

## When adding a tool
engine.ts → Page.tsx → manifest.ts → registry.ts → router.tsx

## Styling pattern
Use inline styles with CSS custom properties only:
  style={{ color: 'var(--color-text-primary)', padding: 'var(--space-4)' }}
Never:
  className="text-blue-500 p-4"
  style={{ color: '#1E3A5F', padding: '16px' }}
